-- Italian Industrial Production Rises for Sixth Month on Economic Recovery
-- Jeffrey Donovan
-- 2010-08-06T08:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/italian-industrial-production-rises-for-sixth-month-on-economic-recovery.html

          
          
             Italian industrial production rose in
June for a sixth month as the recovery from the countryâ€™s worst
recession in six decades advanced.  
 Production climbed 0.6 percent from May, when it rose 1
percent, Rome-based national statistics institute Istat said
today in a report. That was less than the 0.7 percent median
forecast by 18 economists in a Bloomberg News survey. Output
rose 8.1 percent in June from a year earlier, Istat said.  
          
          


  


        